/span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_matrix" title=
=3D"Square matrix">Square matrix</a></div>
<p>A linear <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endomorphism" title=3D=
"Endomorphism">endomorphism</a> is a linear map that maps a vector space <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">V</span> to itself.=
=20
If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">V</span> has a=
 basis of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span=
> elements, such an endomorphism is represented by a square matrix of size =
<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>.
</p><p>Concerning general linear maps, linear endomorphisms, and square mat=
rices have some specific properties that make their study an important part=
 of linear algebra, which is used in many parts of mathematics, including <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_transformation" title=3D"=
Geometric transformation">geometric transformations</a>, <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coordinate_change" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Co=
ordinate change">coordinate changes</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Quadratic_form" title=3D"Quadratic form">quadratic forms</a>, and ma=
ny other parts of mathematics.
</p>
